    <stitle>13 SPEED AND 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-713/18 SERIES - ASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>ASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="3">
            <title>GEAR SHIFT LEVER</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Inspect tension spring and washer for wear. Replace if necessary.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Apply Eaton rust preventative lubricant #71212 or equivalent to the shift lever pivot ball.
                        Refer to GROUP 10 - LUBRICATION in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual for recommended lubes. A
                        lubricant film should cover all surfaces between and including the pivot ball.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure the assembly in a vise with the housing bottom facing up (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13007d3">Figure 133</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f13007d3" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13007d3" filename="../figg13/G13007D3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 133. Secure Assembly in Vise</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the spade pin is damaged, replace and install the new spade pin in housing tower bore
                    (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13007d3">Figure 133</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">In models so equipped, install the nut and washer in the housing bore.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the O-ring is damaged, replace and lubricate the O-ring with Eaton/Fuller lubricant
                    #71206 supplied with the O-ring kit. Install the O-ring in the housing tower inside groove (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13007d3">Figure 133</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the lever ball slot with the spade pin and position the gear shift lever in the
                    housing tower (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13007d4">Figure 134</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f13007d4" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13007d4" filename="../figg13/G13007D4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 134. Position Gear Shift Lever in Housing Tower</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the washer over the ball with dished side up (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13007d4">Figure 134</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a tension spring driver to install the tension spring under the housing lugs (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13007d5">Figure 135</hotlnk>). Seat the tension spring one coil at a time.
                </para>
                <figure id="f13007d5" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13007d5" filename="../figg13/G13007D5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 135. Install Tension Spring</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a rubber boot over the gear shift lever and against the housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Make sure the gear shift lever can move.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
